Class Time

  • java.lang.Object
    • Time
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Time>

    public class Time
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Time>
    Created by Nick Natali on 1/22/17. The Time class represents a particular time of day such as 12:30 PM or 9:47 AM. All Time objects always have a valid state.
